This fall I will be teaching the following graduate cryptology course
at UMBC:

	  CMSC-652 Cryptology and Data Security
	  Tues/Thurs 2:30pm-3:45pm
	  CP 210

Interested parties are welcome to attend.  This course is offered
approximately once every two years.

Topics will include ciphers and their analyses, authentication systems
(including NIST's DSA), key exchange protocols (including
Diffie-Helman), public-key cryptography (including RSA), differential
cryptanalysis of DES, clipper, zero-knowledge complexity, electronic
money, and quantum cryptography.

Students should have an undergraduate CS or Math degree.

Alan T. Sherman
sherman@cs.umbc.edu



